📌 Problem Statement

Traditional calculators require users to manually select arithmetic operators such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. This makes interaction less intuitive and not user-friendly, especially for beginners or non-technical users. Moreover, conventional calculators cannot understand natural language inputs like “add 5 and 3” or “divide 10 by 2”.

The problem is to develop an intelligent system that can:

Understand user intent from text input
Automatically identify the required mathematical operation
Perform calculations without explicit operator selection

This project aims to bridge the gap between human language and machine understanding by integrating Machine Learning into a calculator.

📌 Scope of the Project

The scope of this project includes:

Developing a dual-mode calculator (AI-based and manual mode)
Implementing text classification using Machine Learning
Supporting basic arithmetic operations:
Addition
Subtraction
Multiplication
Division
Enabling natural language input processing
Providing a simple and interactive command-line interface

The project is limited to basic operations and simple sentence structures, making it suitable for beginner-level AI/ML implementation.

📌 Target Users

This project is useful for:

🎓 Students and beginners learning programming or mathematics
👩‍💻 Learners of AI/ML who want to understand practical applications
🧑‍🏫 Educators demonstrating basic NLP and ML concepts
👥 General users who prefer simple, natural language interaction
📌 Limitations
Limited dataset reduces prediction accuracy
Can only understand predefined keywords (add, subtract, etc.)
Cannot process complex or long sentences
Supports only two numbers at a time
No support for advanced mathematical operations (like power, trigonometry)
Works only in text mode (no GUI or voice input)
📌 Applications

This project can be applied in:

🤖 Chatbots and virtual assistants
🎤 Voice-based assistants (with speech integration)
📱 Smart calculator apps
🎓 Educational tools for teaching AI and ML concepts
💬 Conversational interfaces where users interact using natural language
